Toshiba to Invest $37 Million in S. Korean Wind Power Company, NHK Says

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-05-23T08:50:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/toshiba-to-invest-37-million-in-s-korean-wind-power-company-nhk-says.html
Toshiba Corp. (6502)  plans enter the wind
power business by investing as much as 3 billion yen ($37
million) in Unison Co., a South Korean wind power company,
public broadcaster NHK said.  Toshiba will purchase convertible bonds in Unison to
acquire about one-third of its shares in a year, NHK reported on
its website, citing people familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  